1
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:11,110
[lilting classical music plays]

2
00:00:12,910 --> 00:00:14,910
[thunder rumbles distantly]

3
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:33,510
[Rosie] Adam, I'm going to look for Grace.
She's not next door.

4
00:00:39,470 --> 00:00:40,830
[rain pitters gently]

5
00:00:47,270 --> 00:00:48,510
[vehicle approaches]

6
00:00:51,950 --> 00:00:53,870
[ominous music plays]

7
00:00:53,950 --> 00:00:54,990
[car door opens]

8
00:00:57,350 --> 00:00:58,350
Grace!

9
00:01:01,990 --> 00:01:03,430
Grace! Where have you been?

10
00:01:03,510 --> 00:01:06,150
It's okay. She's okay.

11
00:01:06,230 --> 00:01:08,070
I found her playing
outside the Phillipses'.

12
00:01:08,150 --> 00:01:09,710
You can't keep running off like this.

13
00:01:09,790 --> 00:01:13,350
Look, no one needs
to get into any trouble, do they?

14
00:01:13,430 --> 00:01:15,230
[Rosie] Thank you for bringing her home.

15
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:18,870
It's been a tough day for everybody.

16
00:01:21,030 --> 00:01:23,150
I'm so glad we chatted earlier.

17
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:24,390
Me too.

18
00:01:25,470 --> 00:01:27,070
Come on, Grace.

19
00:01:35,670 --> 00:01:37,390
Sit down. I'll do your shoes.

20
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:39,310
[sentimental music plays]

21
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:41,470
You need to get to bed. It's late.

22
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,510
Come on, chickpea.

23
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:48,830
Upstairs.

24
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:58,910
[car approaches]

25
00:02:00,550 --> 00:02:01,390
[engine stops]

26
00:02:01,470 --> 00:02:03,950
[car door opens and closes]

27
00:02:06,910 --> 00:02:07,990
[lock clicks]

28
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:10,350
[front door opens and closes]

29
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:14,070
[menacing music plays]

30
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:34,790
[gasps]

31
00:02:39,390 --> 00:02:40,390
[groans]

32
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:42,470
[sighs]

33
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:46,470
[sighs heavily]

34
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:58,070
Is that better?

35
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:01,070
Have you got a plan, son?

36
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:03,310
You can't keep me tied up forever.

37
00:03:05,510 --> 00:03:06,990
You don't want to be doing this.

38
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:08,830
Sin upon sin.

39
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:11,390
There's good in you.

40
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,310
Find the light.

41
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:14,550
I'm gonna need you to be quiet, all right?

42
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,830
Otherwise, where does this end?

43
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:19,150
[ominous music plays]

44
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:22,510
- [telephone rings]
- [breath catches]

45
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:25,550
[phone stops ringing]

46
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:29,190
[grunts]

47
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:34,110
- [sliding door opens]
- [groans]

48
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,670
[thunder rumbles]

49
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,910
[groans]

50
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:39,910
[Rosie] Adam.

51
00:03:39,990 --> 00:03:41,990
[desolate music plays]

52
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,350
What happened?

53
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:48,310
I ju-- I cut myself…

54
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:50,590
cleaning up.

55
00:03:50,670 --> 00:03:51,790
I'm fine.

56
00:03:55,190 --> 00:03:57,990
You did really well today at the funeral.

57
00:03:58,070 --> 00:03:59,630
Isaac would have been really proud.

58
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:00,910
[chuckles sadly]

59
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,870
[thunder rumbles distantly]

60
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,830
[thunder crashes]

61
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:23,670
[sighs softly]

62
00:04:25,590 --> 00:04:26,950
[dramatic music plays]

63
00:04:27,030 --> 00:04:29,030
[breathing heavily]

64
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:42,990
[somber theme music plays]

65
00:04:50,910 --> 00:04:53,750
["End Of The World"
by Skeeter Davis plays]

66
00:04:55,590 --> 00:04:57,590
[song continues faintly on radio]

67
00:04:57,670 --> 00:05:03,070
♪ Why does the sun go on shining? ♪

68
00:05:04,550 --> 00:05:09,150
♪ Why does the sea rush to shore? ♪

69
00:05:09,230 --> 00:05:10,670
[door opens]

70
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:14,110
♪ Don't they know…? ♪

71
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:15,390
[dramatic music plays]

72
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:16,590
Shit.

73
00:05:22,150 --> 00:05:24,550
- [Mason] What's going on?
- Get me my phone, will you?

74
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:25,630
Why? What happened?

75
00:05:25,710 --> 00:05:28,030
Get me my fucking phone, now!

76
00:05:28,110 --> 00:05:29,030
Okay.

77
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:31,230
Shit.

78
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:36,510
[door closes]

79
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,030
Thank you.

80
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:44,590
She won't eat. She won't speak.

81
00:05:44,670 --> 00:05:46,830
She's barely said a word
since she's woken up.

82
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:49,390
[Adam] Grace? Are you sick?

83
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:51,030
She's not hot.

84
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:54,270
Adam, I don't know what's wrong with her.

85
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:56,670
[telephone rings]

86
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:02,790
- [handset clatters]
- [phone beeps]

87
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:05,350
- Hello.
- [Sam] Adam, I'm at the Phillipses'.

88
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:07,270
Bit of a situation here. [chuckles]

89
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:09,390
Yeah, I need your help.

90
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:11,830
[Adam] Okay. Understood.

91
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:13,510
[tense music plays]

92
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:15,590
- [phone beeps]
- [handset clatters gently]

93
00:06:17,350 --> 00:06:18,550
Mr. Phillips is out.

94
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:20,630
He's broken his confinement.

95
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,830
He needs to atone!

96
00:06:22,910 --> 00:06:25,870
- Do you think she needs a doctor?
- No, I don't think she needs a doctor.

97
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:28,030
I think she needs to do as she's told!

98
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:29,950
Sit down, Grace!

99
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:33,150
- [slaps table]
- Sit down and eat your breakfast.

100
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:35,270
I need to go.

101
00:06:35,350 --> 00:06:36,750
I need to meet Sam.

102
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:38,190
[bowl shatters]

103
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:43,030
How dare you be so willful?!

104
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:03,590
[music intensifies]

105
00:07:03,670 --> 00:07:04,510
[keys jingle]

106
00:07:06,470 --> 00:07:07,430
[lock clicks]

107
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,630
Get back!

108
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,670
This is not what you want
to be doing, Mr. Phillips.

109
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,030
Is it?

110
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:23,510
Come on.

111
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,550
- Give me the gun.
- No.

112
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:28,630
- Come on, just-- just put it down.
- No!

113
00:07:28,710 --> 00:07:29,990
Come on.

114
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:34,550
We don't need this to be
any more difficult, do we?

115
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:35,550
[gun cocks]

116
00:07:37,910 --> 00:07:39,230
Give me the gun.

117
00:07:44,310 --> 00:07:45,150
[Sam whimpers]

118
00:07:45,230 --> 00:07:47,750
It wasn't me. Adam, it wasn't me.

119
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,990
I wasn't driving. It was Sam!

120
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:52,870
- Adam, please, I didn't kill your brother.
- You don't talk about Isaac.

121
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:54,390
- I don-- I didn't!
- You murdered him.

122
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:57,270
- Get him out of here, will you?
- Please! Please, in the name of God!

123
00:07:57,350 --> 00:08:00,310
It was Sam! It was Sam, it was him!

124
00:08:00,390 --> 00:08:02,310
The devil walks among us!

125
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:04,670
- It was him!
- I'll pray for you.

126
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,110
[uneasy music plays]

127
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:07,630
[Mr. Phillips] No! It was him!

128
00:08:08,990 --> 00:08:11,870
It was Sam! It was Sam!

129
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:16,590
[thunder rumbles]

130
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:27,550
[Rosie] Chickpea?

131
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:29,750
I brought you some biscuits.

132
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:34,150
They're here if you get hungry.

133
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:35,909
[dreamy music plays]

134
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,470
I love you.

135
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:51,270
[footsteps recede]

136
00:08:53,310 --> 00:08:55,430
Now she won't even come out her bedroom.

137
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:59,070
Well, she's only six, sweetheart.
She's been through a lot. We all have.

138
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,910
[Rosie] Adam shouldn't
have shouted at her.

139
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:03,030
- Well, you know men.
- No.

140
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:05,670
That's just an excuse. She was upset.

141
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,830
I-I don't know what's wrong with him.
It's like he's…

142
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:11,190
We all have times in our lives, 
Rosie, where it gets too much.

143
00:09:11,790 --> 00:09:14,310
Eh? It's a test. That's all it is.

144
00:09:14,390 --> 00:09:15,630
I don't know, Mum.

145
00:09:16,510 --> 00:09:19,790
I don't know if this place
is good for me, for Grace.

146
00:09:23,350 --> 00:09:26,430
You pray… and God'll show you the way.

147
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:28,670
You're stronger
than you think, sweetheart.

148
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:29,630
And Grace?

149
00:09:29,710 --> 00:09:31,030
[wistful music plays]

150
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:33,830
You pray.

151
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,710
[car doors open]

152
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:42,590
[car door closes]

153
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:45,390
[engine starts]

154
00:10:02,350 --> 00:10:04,350
[birds squawk]

155
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:10,230
[thunder rumbles ominously]

156
00:10:11,710 --> 00:10:13,030
[thunder crashes]

157
00:10:13,110 --> 00:10:15,190
Grace, what's the matter?

158
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:20,030
Is it the funeral?

159
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:24,030
Are you upset about Uncle Isaac?

160
00:10:28,590 --> 00:10:31,150
Grace, you know you can tell me anything.

161
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:37,470
Sam told me it was a game.

162
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,590
But it wasn't.

163
00:10:39,470 --> 00:10:41,590
- They were fighting.
- Who?

164
00:10:42,590 --> 00:10:43,910
Who was fighting?

165
00:10:43,990 --> 00:10:45,310
[tense ethereal music plays]

166
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:48,950
[softly] Sam and Mr. Phillips.

167
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:50,230
What?

168
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:52,950
Why were they fighting?

169
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:56,630
[shushes]

170
00:11:00,990 --> 00:11:03,030
Someone told you not to say anything?

171
00:11:07,590 --> 00:11:08,790
What did you see?

172
00:11:09,790 --> 00:11:11,430
What did Sam say?

173
00:11:14,710 --> 00:11:17,510
I don't think you were supposed
to see what you just saw.

174
00:11:18,270 --> 00:11:19,510
Make sure you don't tell anyone.

175
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:23,070
Not even your mummy.

176
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,750
Otherwise, I'm gonna have
to hurt you, Grace.

177
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,790
[door opens and closes]

178
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:35,110
[Sam] Well, you shouldn't have
any more trouble from him now.

179
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:37,790
Grace.

180
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:40,510
Stay with Teddy and don't leave this room.

181
00:11:40,590 --> 00:11:42,350
[swirling ominous music plays]

182
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:52,750
[Adam] How do you find everything so easy?

183
00:11:53,990 --> 00:11:55,190
[Sam] Find what?

184
00:11:56,070 --> 00:11:58,630
[Adam] Mr. Phillips, taking charge…

185
00:11:59,310 --> 00:12:01,590
[Sam] Well, it's simple for me.

186
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:03,070
This place, 

187
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:05,670
the Fellowship and the rules, 

188
00:12:06,270 --> 00:12:07,750
make sense, you know?

189
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:11,510
But I could see
why you would struggle with it.

190
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:13,870
Your nature.

191
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,910
Maybe it just doesn't work
for you here anymore.

192
00:12:21,790 --> 00:12:24,750
Maybe it's time
to think of a different life…

193
00:12:26,190 --> 00:12:27,030
outside.

194
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:30,350
No, I-- I couldn't. I-- I can't.

195
00:12:31,710 --> 00:12:33,310
It's the unchosen.

196
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,750
Oh. Hey, Rosie.

197
00:12:42,790 --> 00:12:44,550
Would anyone like a tea?

198
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:45,870
No, thank you.

199
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:48,990
[Sam] Aye, a tea'd be grand, thanks.

200
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,950
What, did youse hear?

201
00:12:52,030 --> 00:12:54,190
Uh, Mrs. Phillips…

202
00:12:54,990 --> 00:12:56,190
walked out.

203
00:12:57,830 --> 00:12:59,270
Left her husband.

204
00:12:59,350 --> 00:13:00,550
[kettle roiling]

205
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:02,590
No, I didn't.

206
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:05,430
[Sam] People…

207
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,630
are a mystery, huh?

208
00:13:11,310 --> 00:13:13,670
Especially the ones you think you know.

209
00:13:20,350 --> 00:13:21,910
I'm gonna check on Grace.

210
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,750
[disquieting music plays]

211
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:35,110
[door closes]

212
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:48,630
[water running]

213
00:13:49,910 --> 00:13:52,310
I want to thank you
for letting me in your house.

214
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:54,150
[Rosie's breath trembles]

215
00:13:55,110 --> 00:13:56,710
I know it's been difficult.

216
00:14:11,310 --> 00:14:12,310
Rosie?

217
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:13,470
[faucet squeaks]

218
00:14:14,350 --> 00:14:15,510
What-- What's the matter?

219
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:17,390
Nothing.

220
00:14:17,470 --> 00:14:18,990
Just… not here.

221
00:14:20,310 --> 00:14:22,910
[thunder rumbles]

222
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:26,350
Don't tell me
you're scared of storms. [chuckles]

223
00:14:28,350 --> 00:14:30,950
It's just God moving his furniture.

224
00:14:42,910 --> 00:14:44,510
When you pulled away, 

225
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:47,430
I thought I'd lost you.

226
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,590
[Sam's breath catches]

227
00:14:51,310 --> 00:14:53,310
Ah, I couldn't fucking bear it.

228
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:55,990
I need to go.

229
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,150
Grace, she's been upset.

230
00:15:00,830 --> 00:15:01,910
About what?

231
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:06,670
Isaac, her uncle.

232
00:15:09,070 --> 00:15:10,590
[sighs softly] Yeah.

233
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:35,630
I'll see you tonight.

234
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:38,710
At the meeting.

235
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:40,110
I'd like that.

236
00:15:47,510 --> 00:15:48,790
I can't do it, Rosie.

237
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:52,310
I can't live without you.

238
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:55,270
[thunder rumbles]

239
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:10,190
[lock clicks]

240
00:16:10,910 --> 00:16:11,950
[sighs]

241
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:14,630
[breathing heavily]

242
00:16:14,710 --> 00:16:16,750
[serene music plays and fades]

243
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:24,310
[Adam] "…servants of Saul."

244
00:16:24,390 --> 00:16:28,830
"Face-to-face, 
as a man speaks to his friend."

245
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:31,950
"And he would return to the camp…"

246
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:34,950
Adam, Grace told me
something you need to know.

247
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:38,350
She saw Mr. Phillips
and Sam fighting last night.

248
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:40,750
Mr. Phillips said that Sam killed Isaac.

249
00:16:40,830 --> 00:16:43,870
He's a drunk. And a killer.
Of course he would say that.

250
00:16:43,950 --> 00:16:45,190
Adam, it's true.

251
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:47,790
That doesn't make sense.
Why would Sam want to kill Isaac?

252
00:16:47,870 --> 00:16:50,550
Because that's who he is, what he does.

253
00:16:50,630 --> 00:16:52,870
He murdered a girl
in Ireland when he was 16.

254
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:54,710
That's why he was in prison.

255
00:16:55,230 --> 00:16:56,790
Then he killed her cousin.

256
00:16:57,670 --> 00:17:00,390
Isaac must have found out.
That's why he came round.

257
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:05,470
To warn us?

258
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:11,390
And I sent him away?

259
00:17:15,430 --> 00:17:17,950
But you think that's why Sam killed him?

260
00:17:18,950 --> 00:17:20,950
He didn't want us to know.

261
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:22,950
He didn't want me to know.

262
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,589
[thunder rumbles]

263
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:27,829
Why you?

264
00:17:35,310 --> 00:17:36,670
I slept with Sam.

265
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:41,550
[tender music plays]

266
00:17:44,390 --> 00:17:45,590
We were…

267
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:47,030
together.

268
00:17:47,710 --> 00:17:49,150
Did he make you?

269
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:51,630
No.

270
00:17:53,470 --> 00:17:55,590
I wanted to.
I was the one that went to him.

271
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,150
I started it.

272
00:17:58,830 --> 00:18:00,190
[thunder rumbles]

273
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:01,630
I know it's wrong.

274
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:04,430
I know it's a sin. I--

275
00:18:04,510 --> 00:18:05,830
We are married, Rosie!

276
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:07,510
Are we?

277
00:18:09,430 --> 00:18:11,070
You love Grace. I know you do.

278
00:18:12,270 --> 00:18:14,350
You love the idea of a wife.

279
00:18:14,950 --> 00:18:18,670
But when we sleep together
and you don't even look at me…

280
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:20,230
It's not… [sighs]

281
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:23,630
I'm not what you had with him.

282
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,590
- [thunder rumbles]
- [electricity crackles]

283
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:28,430
[Grace] Mummy!

284
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:30,310
I'm coming.

285
00:18:30,390 --> 00:18:31,350
[Adam sniffles]

286
00:18:31,430 --> 00:18:32,830
Adam, please.

287
00:18:33,790 --> 00:18:36,910
Please, I'm not telling you this
to hurt you, I'm not.

288
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:39,470
I just need you to understand all of it.

289
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:42,790
And even if you can't, 
the only thing that matters is Grace.

290
00:18:42,870 --> 00:18:44,550
She's terrified.

291
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:46,830
She knows what Sam's done.

292
00:18:46,910 --> 00:18:48,350
And he threatened her.

293
00:18:48,910 --> 00:18:50,310
Our daughter.

294
00:18:52,310 --> 00:18:54,310
Adam, he said that he'd hurt her.

295
00:18:54,390 --> 00:18:56,390
[suspenseful music plays]

296
00:18:59,230 --> 00:19:01,230
[alarm beeping rapidly]

297
00:19:04,790 --> 00:19:06,350
- What's that?
- Smoke alarm.

298
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:08,630
The power's out. Phone's dead too.

299
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:09,950
And what if he comes back?

300
00:19:11,390 --> 00:19:12,670
We need to get away.

301
00:19:13,190 --> 00:19:15,470
Now, take Grace. Get her somewhere safe.

302
00:19:23,790 --> 00:19:24,990
Thank you.

303
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,590
Grace? You need to be quick.

304
00:19:29,670 --> 00:19:31,830
- We have to go.
- [Adam] I'll drive you to Norwich.

305
00:19:31,910 --> 00:19:34,270
My father's cousin, Martin, 
he's the Elder there.

306
00:19:41,070 --> 00:19:43,110
Rosie, what are you doing?

307
00:19:48,550 --> 00:19:50,150
[softly] We're not going to Norwich.

308
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:53,190
Why not?

309
00:19:55,190 --> 00:19:57,030
You can take us to the station.

310
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:01,190
I don't understand.

311
00:20:02,550 --> 00:20:03,710
I'm leaving.

312
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:06,870
And I'm taking Grace.
We're leaving the Fellowship.

313
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:08,630
[bittersweet music plays]

314
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:09,950
Rosie?

315
00:20:11,430 --> 00:20:12,470
No.

316
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:16,590
No. No, you can't. You can't.

317
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:18,950
- We're meant to be a family.
- Yeah, but we can fix this.

318
00:20:19,030 --> 00:20:21,230
This place, it takes all the good
and the love and turns--

319
00:20:21,310 --> 00:20:23,550
- You can't take Grace from me.
- …into damage and control.

320
00:20:23,630 --> 00:20:26,310
We can fix this. I-I-I--
I know the marriage… I know Sam…

321
00:20:26,390 --> 00:20:27,670
But you can't.

322
00:20:33,630 --> 00:20:34,710
You were…

323
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:37,510
You were planning on leaving me anyway?

324
00:20:42,150 --> 00:20:43,190
With him?

325
00:20:43,830 --> 00:20:45,270
Not at first.

326
00:20:45,350 --> 00:20:46,990
Just me, Grace.

327
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:50,230
[Adam sighs softly]

328
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:52,710
Why?

329
00:21:03,670 --> 00:21:05,030
[Adam exhales heavily]

330
00:21:10,990 --> 00:21:12,190
[gasps]

331
00:21:17,310 --> 00:21:18,510
You hurt me.

332
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,990
Humiliated me.

333
00:21:25,230 --> 00:21:27,310
You looked at me like you hated me.

334
00:21:27,390 --> 00:21:28,430
[Adam gasps]

335
00:21:32,910 --> 00:21:34,230
[sighs softly]

336
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:38,910
I don't hate you.

337
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:42,110
[whimpers softly]

338
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:46,070
I…

339
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:48,750
I hate…

340
00:21:52,190 --> 00:21:54,110
You deserve better than me.

341
00:22:00,710 --> 00:22:02,390
You deserve a better husband.

342
00:22:02,470 --> 00:22:04,470
[tender music plays]

343
00:22:06,750 --> 00:22:08,190
Where will you go?

344
00:22:12,630 --> 00:22:13,870
But you have a plan?

345
00:22:20,750 --> 00:22:23,510
I can… still see her?

346
00:22:24,630 --> 00:22:26,590
Or just visit Grace?

347
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:34,630
Or just write to her, maybe.

348
00:22:37,870 --> 00:22:39,430
That's up to you.

349
00:22:42,870 --> 00:22:44,470
You'll tell her about me?

350
00:22:46,470 --> 00:22:48,630
If she asked, just…

351
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:51,950
just tell her how much I love her.

352
00:22:54,470 --> 00:22:56,430
[breathes shakily]

353
00:22:59,230 --> 00:23:00,710
'Cause that part is true.

354
00:23:18,670 --> 00:23:20,190
Is Daddy coming?

355
00:23:24,310 --> 00:23:25,470
[luggage thuds gently]

356
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:27,630
It's just you.

357
00:23:29,270 --> 00:23:30,590
You and Mummy.

358
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:33,350
["All My Tears" by Ane Brun plays]

359
00:23:36,990 --> 00:23:39,790
♪ When I go, don't cry for me ♪

360
00:23:39,870 --> 00:23:42,990
♪ In my father's arms I'll be ♪

361
00:23:43,070 --> 00:23:44,230
[Grace sobs gently]

362
00:23:44,310 --> 00:23:47,470
♪ The wounds this world left on my soul ♪

363
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:51,070
♪ Will all be healed and I'll be whole… ♪

364
00:23:52,790 --> 00:23:54,550
Let's get you in your seat, yeah?

365
00:23:55,270 --> 00:23:58,870
♪ With the light of Jesus's face ♪

366
00:24:00,070 --> 00:24:02,870
♪ And I will not be ashamed ♪

367
00:24:02,950 --> 00:24:06,350
♪ For my savior knows my name ♪

368
00:24:07,310 --> 00:24:12,230
♪ It don't matter where you bury me ♪

369
00:24:13,670 --> 00:24:17,150
♪ I'll be home and I'll be free ♪

370
00:24:17,870 --> 00:24:22,710
♪ It don't matter anywhere I lay ♪

371
00:24:24,350 --> 00:24:28,310
♪ All my tears be washed away ♪

372
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:35,230
♪ Gold and silver blind the eye ♪

373
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:38,510
♪ Temporary riches lie ♪

374
00:24:38,590 --> 00:24:39,670
[engine starts]

375
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:43,070
♪ Come and eat from heaven's store ♪

376
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:46,510
♪ Come and drink and thirst no more ♪

377
00:24:47,710 --> 00:24:50,510
♪ So weep not for me, my friend ♪

378
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:54,470
♪ When my time below does end ♪

379
00:24:55,550 --> 00:24:58,070
♪ For my life belongs to Him ♪

380
00:24:58,150 --> 00:25:01,830
♪ Who will raise the dead again ♪

381
00:25:02,590 --> 00:25:07,470
♪ It don't matter where you bury me ♪

382
00:25:08,830 --> 00:25:11,990
♪ I'll be home and I'll be free ♪

383
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:16,110
[ominous music plays]

384
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:39,350
- Adam.
- I know.

385
00:25:40,430 --> 00:25:42,190
- Turn around.
- I can't.

386
00:25:43,190 --> 00:25:46,590
Grace, give me your hearing aid.
Grace, hearing aid now!

387
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:55,790
Bloody Armageddon out here.

388
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:57,750
Where youse off to?

389
00:25:57,830 --> 00:26:00,030
Hospital. Audiology.

390
00:26:00,110 --> 00:26:02,190
Grace has broken her hearing aid.

391
00:26:07,150 --> 00:26:08,470
Have you any tools in the back?

392
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:10,150
No.

393
00:26:10,230 --> 00:26:13,030
A chainsaw, I reckon we can move
that thing, just the two of us.

394
00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:15,070
We haven't got anything. Sam.

395
00:26:15,990 --> 00:26:18,230
- Take Grace and run.
- [seatbelts clicks]

396
00:26:27,910 --> 00:26:29,070
- [Adam yells]
- [groans]

397
00:26:29,150 --> 00:26:31,470
You killed my brother! [grunts]

398
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,470
You fucking…

399
00:26:32,550 --> 00:26:33,790
[Sam grunts]

400
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:37,630
[exclaims]

401
00:26:38,550 --> 00:26:40,070
- [yells]
- [groans]

402
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:42,270
- [grunts]
- [groans]

403
00:26:42,830 --> 00:26:45,150
[panting]

404
00:26:52,070 --> 00:26:53,750
[suspenseful music plays]

405
00:26:53,830 --> 00:26:55,070
[Rosie pants]

406
00:27:02,670 --> 00:27:03,550
Grace, come on.

407
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:05,910
- [Grace] I can't.
- Rosie!

408
00:27:08,350 --> 00:27:09,550
[sighs]

409
00:27:09,630 --> 00:27:11,430
- [Rosie] Shh. Shh.
- Rosie!

410
00:27:13,550 --> 00:27:15,430
- Mummy. Mummy.
- Shh.

411
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:16,790
Rosie!

412
00:27:18,150 --> 00:27:20,510
[Grace whimpers]

413
00:27:20,590 --> 00:27:22,590
[tense ethereal music plays]

414
00:27:24,190 --> 00:27:25,390
Grace!

415
00:27:25,470 --> 00:27:28,350
Oh, Grace, 
you must be so cold, sweetheart!

416
00:27:29,710 --> 00:27:31,750
I'm sorry if I scared you.

417
00:27:38,630 --> 00:27:40,870
- [Rosie, softly] Go, go, go.
- [Grace grunts]

418
00:27:43,830 --> 00:27:46,550
[Rosie and Grace grunt]

419
00:27:48,430 --> 00:27:49,510
Watch your head.

420
00:27:50,750 --> 00:27:51,870
Come on, Grace.

421
00:27:51,950 --> 00:27:53,670
- Mummy, please.
- Grace, come on.

422
00:27:54,590 --> 00:27:57,270
Grace, look at me.
We need to get to Daddy's office.

423
00:27:57,350 --> 00:27:59,910
Get the keys to one of the vans.
Chickpea, please.

424
00:27:59,990 --> 00:28:01,510
- [Sam] Rosie!
- [gasps]

425
00:28:02,670 --> 00:28:04,470
Okay. Okay, come on.

426
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:06,550
Come on, you hide in here.

427
00:28:07,270 --> 00:28:09,470
You stay there. You hear me?

428
00:28:09,550 --> 00:28:12,110
You stay there, 
and you don't come out until I come back.

429
00:28:14,710 --> 00:28:15,550
I'm sorry.

430
00:28:15,630 --> 00:28:17,190
[sentimental music plays]

431
00:28:20,190 --> 00:28:21,590
I'll be two minutes.

432
00:28:22,110 --> 00:28:23,430
[suspenseful music plays]

433
00:28:45,630 --> 00:28:47,630
[footsteps approach]

434
00:28:50,790 --> 00:28:51,790
Don't.

435
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:57,150
Don't run.

436
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:02,550
Grace told me about Isaac.

437
00:29:04,430 --> 00:29:05,310
I'm sorry.

438
00:29:08,270 --> 00:29:10,230
I'm sorry, I didn't have a choice.

439
00:29:11,790 --> 00:29:13,230
He was gonna tell you…

440
00:29:14,510 --> 00:29:15,590
everything.

441
00:29:17,430 --> 00:29:18,510
I couldn't have that.

442
00:29:19,590 --> 00:29:21,030
So you killed him?

443
00:29:23,270 --> 00:29:25,390
Rosie, please. Please, 
don't look at me like that, okay?

444
00:29:25,990 --> 00:29:26,870
Don't.

445
00:29:28,110 --> 00:29:30,910
- You-- You threatened Grace.
- No, no, no, I never would do that.

446
00:29:30,990 --> 00:29:33,470
- You said you'd hurt her.
- What? Hurt Grace?

447
00:29:33,990 --> 00:29:36,430
No, I would never hurt her.
I would never hurt any child.

448
00:29:36,510 --> 00:29:38,910
Come on, Rosie, you have to believe me.

449
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:44,270
They're just fucking words!
I just said it.

450
00:29:44,350 --> 00:29:46,430
Like you said you'd keep me safe!

451
00:29:46,510 --> 00:29:48,750
That I never had to be frightened of you.

452
00:29:49,270 --> 00:29:50,230
[thunder rumbles]

453
00:29:50,310 --> 00:29:52,470
- 'Cause I am.
- You're not frightened of me. Come on.

454
00:29:52,550 --> 00:29:54,150
I'm frightened.

455
00:29:57,870 --> 00:29:58,990
Love you--

456
00:29:59,510 --> 00:30:01,150
I love you, Rosie.

457
00:30:01,230 --> 00:30:03,230
[disquieting music plays]

458
00:30:04,270 --> 00:30:05,310
Rosie?

459
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:10,430
[whimpers and sniffles]

460
00:30:10,950 --> 00:30:13,110
[groans] And I don't know what to do.

461
00:30:16,670 --> 00:30:17,950
It's not my fault, okay?

462
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:19,670
How can you say that?

463
00:30:19,750 --> 00:30:22,510
Because there's something
wrong with me, Rosie.

464
00:30:22,590 --> 00:30:25,150
I'm fucking wired wrong.

465
00:30:25,230 --> 00:30:27,790
I get this-- this noise in my head, 

466
00:30:27,870 --> 00:30:29,830
and I can't control it, and…

467
00:30:30,870 --> 00:30:33,750
Rosie, come on! I just want to talk!

468
00:30:33,830 --> 00:30:35,830
[dramatic music plays]

469
00:30:42,630 --> 00:30:43,830
Rosie!

470
00:30:51,630 --> 00:30:54,310
[exclaims] No, Sam! Sam, leave me!

471
00:30:55,030 --> 00:30:56,630
[grunts and exclaims]

472
00:30:57,270 --> 00:30:59,910
Sam, please! No, please.

473
00:30:59,990 --> 00:31:01,030
No, please, please!

474
00:31:01,110 --> 00:31:02,590
Please, I promise.

475
00:31:03,190 --> 00:31:05,150
What? What do you promise?

476
00:31:05,750 --> 00:31:07,630
I promise I won't leave you.

477
00:31:10,190 --> 00:31:11,390
No.

478
00:31:12,510 --> 00:31:13,950
No, you're lying.

479
00:31:14,590 --> 00:31:16,750
Uh, you're a liar, Rosie.

480
00:31:17,510 --> 00:31:19,670
You're just like the rest
of them, aren't you?

481
00:31:20,430 --> 00:31:22,070
Like my ma.

482
00:31:22,150 --> 00:31:23,350
Like Aisling.

483
00:31:24,470 --> 00:31:27,550
No, you-- you lie
and you fucking leave me.

484
00:31:27,630 --> 00:31:28,550
[sobs]

485
00:31:28,630 --> 00:31:30,830
You lie and you fucking leave me.

486
00:31:30,910 --> 00:31:34,670
[sobs] You lie and you fucking leave me!

487
00:31:34,750 --> 00:31:35,990
[Sam wails]

488
00:31:36,070 --> 00:31:37,150
[screams]

489
00:31:37,230 --> 00:31:41,190
[Sam wails]

490
00:31:46,830 --> 00:31:48,830
[dreamy music plays]

491
00:31:59,830 --> 00:32:02,110
[Sam] "Repent." What does that mean?

492
00:32:02,990 --> 00:32:04,630
[Rosie] It means to be sorry.

493
00:32:06,310 --> 00:32:08,670
Truly sorry for what you've done.

494
00:32:10,510 --> 00:32:12,390
And it means you want to change.

495
00:32:14,710 --> 00:32:17,670
[high-pitched ringing plays and swells]

496
00:32:18,630 --> 00:32:20,030
[Rosie gasps]

497
00:32:20,750 --> 00:32:22,350
[coughs]

498
00:32:22,430 --> 00:32:23,710
[Sam groans]

499
00:32:23,790 --> 00:32:26,310
[Rosie continues coughing]

500
00:32:26,390 --> 00:32:29,270
[both breathing heavily]

501
00:32:30,150 --> 00:32:32,030
I'm going to get Grace now.

502
00:32:32,870 --> 00:32:34,710
And you're going to stay there.

503
00:32:34,790 --> 00:32:36,510
[droning music plays]

504
00:32:38,470 --> 00:32:40,030
You said you loved me, 

505
00:32:40,630 --> 00:32:42,070
so let us leave.

506
00:32:52,150 --> 00:32:54,150
[music turns sweeping and hopeful]

507
00:33:14,550 --> 00:33:16,230
[music turns ominous and fades]

508
00:33:16,310 --> 00:33:17,590
[Adam] Don't move.

509
00:33:28,070 --> 00:33:30,150
Thou shalt not kill.

510
00:33:31,310 --> 00:33:32,950
Come on, even I know that one.

511
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:40,230
Just put the gun down, Adam, 

512
00:33:41,150 --> 00:33:42,790
and call the police on me.

513
00:33:46,790 --> 00:33:47,630
Go on.

514
00:33:51,590 --> 00:33:53,590
[solemn music plays]

515
00:34:04,470 --> 00:34:05,590
[gasps softly]

516
00:34:06,870 --> 00:34:08,190
[gasps]

517
00:34:11,750 --> 00:34:12,830
[whimpers]

518
00:34:15,350 --> 00:34:18,030
All I had to do was manipulate you, Adam.

519
00:34:19,870 --> 00:34:21,750
'Cause that's who you are.

520
00:34:21,830 --> 00:34:23,949
["Fuel To Fire" by Agnes Obel plays]

521
00:34:29,670 --> 00:34:33,190
♪ Do you want me on your mind ♪

522
00:34:33,270 --> 00:34:38,630
♪ Or do you want me to go on? ♪

523
00:34:41,790 --> 00:34:48,110
♪ I might be yours, as sure as I can say ♪

524
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:52,630
♪ Be gone, be faraway ♪

525
00:34:55,270 --> 00:35:00,390
♪ Ooh, ooh, ah-ooh, ooh ♪

526
00:35:02,670 --> 00:35:05,590
♪ Ooh, ooh, ah-ooh, ooh ♪

527
00:35:05,670 --> 00:35:09,070
[woman reads] "The Lord himself
shall descend from heaven with a shout, 

528
00:35:09,790 --> 00:35:11,790
with the voice of the Archangel, 

529
00:35:12,750 --> 00:35:14,910
and with the trumpet-call of God."

530
00:35:16,510 --> 00:35:19,110
"And the dead in Christ shall rise first."

531
00:35:19,710 --> 00:35:22,710
"After that, we which
are still alive and remain

532
00:35:22,790 --> 00:35:26,030
shall be caught up
together with them in the clouds

533
00:35:26,870 --> 00:35:29,070
to meet the Lord
in the air." [audio fades]

534
00:35:31,910 --> 00:35:34,150
[woman on PA]
We're about to begin boarding.

535
00:35:34,230 --> 00:35:36,230
First crossing, Liverpool to Belfast.

536
00:35:36,310 --> 00:35:39,350
♪ Roses on parade ♪

537
00:35:39,430 --> 00:35:44,230
♪ They follow you around ♪

538
00:35:47,910 --> 00:35:53,910
♪ Upon your shore, as sure as I can say ♪

539
00:35:53,990 --> 00:35:58,030
♪ Be gone, be faraway ♪

540
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:05,790
♪ Ooh, ooh, ah-ooh, ooh ♪

541
00:36:05,870 --> 00:36:12,430
♪ Like fuel to fire ♪

542
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:17,790
[tense droning music plays]

543
00:36:46,270 --> 00:36:50,910
